article.headline: Valparaiso 70, Niagara 58
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Urule Igbavboa scored 19 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Valparaiso in a 70-58 non-conference win over Niagara Saturday. Samuel Haanpaa had a career-high 15 points and Shawn Huff added 10 points for the Crusaders (3-0), who won despite committing 20 turnovers. Valparaiso led 50-48 with just over five minutes left before going on a 12-3 run to seal the win. Shawn Huff and Haanpaa hit back to-back 3-pointers to give the Crusaders a 60-51 lead. Niagara got no closer than seven points after that. Niagara (0-2) had a pair of freshmen record career highs in scoring. Tyrone Lewis had 15 points and Rydell Brooks had 12 points. Clif Brown also scored 12 points for the Purple Eagles. Niagara was 2-of-26 (7.7 percent) from 3-point range for the game.
